songs.title: Computer Science I
songs.description: Introductory computer science course where I learned basic programming concepts while working with Python.

songs.title: Computer Science II
songs.description:
Introductory computer science course where I furthered basic programming concepts within Object-Oriented Programming using Java. Notable projects:
Arboles - Programmed a simple outline for a Virtual Machine capable of processing and executing low-level MAQ instructions using an instruction stack and symbol table,
Puzzle Solver / Hoppers Game - Programmed a puzzle solver using a Depth First Search for solving simple problem-solving games and encoded the game 'Hoppers' to be playable in both the command line and a GUI version. This game featured a 'Hint' option that utilized the Depth First Search solver to find the most optimal game path to reach a win and display the next possible option for it.

songs.title: Mechanics of Programming
songs.description:
Introduction to low-level programming and memory management using C. Notable Projects:
HashADT: Developed a Hash Table implementation, showcasing expertise in data abstraction.
Bracetopia: Programmed grid city simulation where two groups are placed randomly, the simulation calculates 'happiness' based on neighbor proximity and proceeds to move the members of the simulation. Features dynamic adjustments via command line and can run for preset cycles or indefinitely using 'curses'.
Amici: Constructed a 'social network' program that manages user interactions such as adding, removing, and friending. Capable of processing input from files or command line and displaying network statistics.
Asteroids: Coded a simplified version of 'Asteroids' using 'curses' and multi-thread programming.
